SIMPLE: pilotage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pilotage
<hw>Pi"lot*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pilotage</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The pilot's skill or
knowledge, as of coasts, rocks, bars, and channels.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir W. Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The compensation made or allowed to a
pilot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Guidance, as by a pilot.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pilot balloon</ent>⟦br⟧
